<br><br>
<p class='title2'>A word about R</p>
<table>
<tr><td class="text11pt" valign="top" align="justify"> 
	Goulphar is written in R, a language that enable statistical and graphical programming. It is very close to the language S+. R is freely available for Windows, MacOs and Linux. Source codes and packages are available on the <a href="http://cran.r-project.org" target="_blank">R project site</a>. The role of R in biology is more and more important, packages are developped to fit biological questions, especially in large scale biology. A R project called <a href="http://www.bioconductor.org/" target="_blank">bioconductor</a> is fully dedicated to bioarrays. It bundles a large set of packages to help in normalizing and analyzing bioarray data.
</td></tr>
</table>

<!--Script to display the general footer on each web page (last update, e-mail references and address)-->
